---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Orbit"
  description="Orbit helps you remember people, context, and follow-ups without turning your relationships into a spreadsheet."
>
  <style>
    .hero {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1.15fr 0.85fr;
      gap: 28px;
      align-items: stretch;
    }

    .hero-copy,
    .hero-card,
    .feature-card,
    .principles,
    .cta {
      padding: 32px;
    }

    .hero-copy {
      position: relative;
      overflow: hidden;
    }

    .eyebrow {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 10px;
      margin-bottom: 18px;
      color: var(--accent-strong);
      font-size: 0.82rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: 0.16em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
    }

    .eyebrow::before {
      content: "";
      width: 42px;
      height: 1px;
      background: linear-gradient(90deg, transparent, var(--accent));
    }

    h1 {
      max-width: 11ch;
      margin: 0;
      font-size: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 5.8rem);
      line-height: 0.92;
      letter-spacing: -0.05em;
    }

    .lede {
      max-width: 36rem;
      margin: 22px 0 0;
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 1.14rem;
    }

    .actions {
      display: flex;
      gap: 14px;
      margin-top: 30px;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
    }

    .button {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      min-height: 50px;
      padding: 0 18px;
      border-radius: 999px;
      border: 1px solid var(--line-strong);
      font-weight: 700;
    }

    .button.primary {
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #d8eeff, #86c0ff);
      color: #0b1730;
      box-shadow: 0 16px 36px rgba(141, 196, 255, 0.22);
    }

    .button.secondary {
      background: rgba(141, 196, 255, 0.08);
      color: var(--text);
    }

    .microcopy {
      margin-top: 16px;
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 0.94rem;
    }

    .hero-card {
      display: grid;
      gap: 18px;
      background:
        radial-gradient(circle at top, rgba(140, 194, 255, 0.18), transparent 30%),
        linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(20, 34, 58, 0.94), rgba(11, 20, 37, 0.96));
    }

    .orbit-mark {
      display: grid;
      place-items: center;
      min-height: 220px;
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: 24px;
      background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(9, 19, 35, 0.92), rgba(10, 18, 32, 0.72));
      box-shadow: inset 0 1px 0 rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.04);
    }

    .orbit-mark img {
      width: min(260px, 72%);
    }

    .stat-line {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
      gap: 12px;
    }

    .stat {
      padding: 14px;
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: 18px;
      background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03);
    }

    .stat strong {
      display: block;
      font-size: 1.1rem;
    }

    .stat span {
      display: block;
      margin-top: 6px;
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 0.92rem;
    }

    .grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
      gap: 20px;
      margin-top: 20px;
    }

    .feature-card {
      min-height: 240px;
    }

    .feature-card h2 {
      margin: 0 0 12px;
      font-size: 1.4rem;
    }

    .feature-card p,
    .principles p,
    .principles li,
    .cta p {
      color: var(--muted);
    }

    .feature-kicker {
      display: inline-block;
      margin-bottom: 16px;
      color: var(--accent-strong);
      font-size: 0.78rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.14em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
    }

    .principles-wrap {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 0.92fr;
      gap: 20px;
      margin-top: 20px;
    }

    .principles h2,
    .cta h2 {
      margin-top: 0;
      font-size: 1.8rem;
    }

    .principles ul {
      margin: 18px 0 0;
      padding-left: 18px;
    }

    .cta {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      justify-content: space-between;
      gap: 18px;
      background:
        radial-gradient(circle at 100% 0, rgba(141, 196, 255, 0.18), transparent 28%),
        linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(17, 31, 53, 0.95), rgba(11, 18, 32, 0.98));
    }

    .small-links {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: 12px;
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }

    .small-links a {
      color: var(--accent-strong);
    }

    @media (max-width: 960px) {
      .hero,
      .principles-wrap,
      .grid {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }
    }

    @media (max-width: 720px) {
      .hero-copy,
      .hero-card,
      .feature-card,
      .principles,
      .cta {
        padding: 24px;
      }

      .stat-line {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }
    }
  </style>

  <div class="container">
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="hero-copy panel">
        <div class="eyebrow">Private by default</div>
        <h1>Remember people like they matter.</h1>
        <p class="lede">
          Orbit is a personal CRM for keeping the human details close: where you met, what matters
          to them, and when to follow up. No feeds. No team dashboard. No growth hacks.
        </p>
        <div class="actions">
          <a class="button primary" href="mailto:vividh999@gmail.com">Get updates</a>
          <a class="button secondary" href="/privacy">Read privacy policy</a>
        </div>
        <p class="microcopy">
          Built for founders, operators, and anyone tired of forgetting context after a good
          conversation.
        </p>
      </div>

      <aside class="hero-card panel" aria-label="Orbit overview">
        <div class="orbit-mark">
          <img src="/orbit-logo.svg" alt="Orbit logo" />
        </div>
        <div class="stat-line">
          <div class="stat">
            <strong>Local-first</strong>
            <span>Your notes stay on your device.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stat">
            <strong>Fast capture</strong>
            <span>People, notes, tags, and follow-ups.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stat">
            <strong>No noise</strong>
            <span>No ads, no analytics, no social layer.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </section>

    <section class="grid" aria-label="Orbit features">
      <article class="feature-card panel">
        <span class="feature-kicker">Memory</span>
        <h2>Keep the context, not just the contact.</h2>
        <p>
          Save the moments that actually matter: what you talked about, where you met, what to ask
          next time, and what you promised.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="feature-card panel">
        <span class="feature-kicker">Follow-up</span>
        <h2>Stop relying on vague mental reminders.</h2>
        <p>
          Orbit makes follow-ups visible without turning your relationships into a sales funnel. It
          is built for memory, not pipeline theater.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="feature-card panel">
        <span class="feature-kicker">Control</span>
        <h2>Private by design.</h2>
        <p>
          Orbit is designed around personal ownership. No account is required, and the current app
          stores your information locally instead of sending it to a remote service.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="principles-wrap">
      <div class="principles panel">
        <h2>Why Orbit exists</h2>
        <p>
          Most relationship tools feel built for reporting upward. Orbit is built for one person
          trying to be more thoughtful with the people around them.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Remember details without clutter.</li>
          <li>Capture notes immediately after a conversation.</li>
          <li>Keep a clear sense of who needs a follow-up.</li>
          <li>Treat privacy as a product feature, not a legal afterthought.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="cta panel">
        <div>
          <h2>Orbit is for real relationships.</h2>
          <p>
            Personal CRM should feel calm, lightweight, and respectful. That is the standard this
            product is aiming for.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="small-links">
          <a href="/privacy">Privacy policy</a>
          <a href="mailto:vividh999@gmail.com">vividh999@gmail.com</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
